## Roles (highest to lowest permission)
1. Admin    → platform owner (me), controls all agencies
2. Owner    → agency owner, sees all operators
3. Operator → creates trips, manages routes/passengers
4. Driver   → backup for conductor
5. Conductor → runs live trips, sends GPS
6. Passenger → receives alerts

## Database Tables
agencies, users, refresh_tokens, audit_logs,
routes, stops, trips, trip_passengers,
conductor_locations, alert_logs,
billing_config, agency_balances,
billing_transactions

## Key Business Logic
GPS Flow:
Conductor phone → GPS every 10s → backend
→ PostGIS ST_DWithin check → trigger radius 10km
→ Redis alert_queue → alert worker
→ Exotel call x2 → MSG91 SMS → Gupshup WhatsApp
→ Conductor manual notification

Alert Cascade:
Exotel call (attempt 1) → wait 30s
→ Exotel call (attempt 2) → fail
→ MSG91 SMS → fail
→ Gupshup WhatsApp → fail
→ Socket.IO conductor_manual_required

Heartbeat:
Every 30s check active trips
If conductor GPS silent > 2min
→ emit conductor_offline to driver
→ Driver takeover flow activates

Billing:
Trip completes → deduct price_per_trip
from agency balance
Default: ₹100 per trip
Low balance → emit balance_low to owner

## Auth Flow (Mobile)
Welcome screen → Phone/Email + Password
→ OTP sent (Brevo email / MSG91 phone)
→ OTP verify → temp_token
→ Agency invite code (optional, skippable)
→ Profile setup → Complete signup
→ Role-based dashboard redirect

Login: Phone/Email + Password OR OTP login

## Code Standards
- TypeScript everywhere (web + backend)
- API response: { success, data, error, meta }
- All routes role-protected from day one
- No hardcoded values → .env always
- Parameterized queries only (Drizzle ORM)
- All timestamps: IST (Asia/Kolkata)
- Phone numbers: E.164 format (+91XXXXXXXXXX)
- Offline support in conductor Flutter app
- Audit log on every state change

